And accomplished excellent Not in the Sanskrit. enlightenment for the
                            sake of the world. Following the Sanskrit pañca­gati­bhrama­bhrāmita sattvān, we emend ’khyams
                                    pas to ’khyams pa’i. {110}

The supreme, unsurpassable message.’ In the Sanskrit text, this verse
                                contains six pādas instead of the usual four. The last pāda (eṣatā padavaraṃ
                                    hyanuttaram) is missing in the Tibetan and is translated from the Sanskrit. {243}
